1) Introduction:
1.1 Document Purpose:
This document aims to outline the requirements for a Railway Reservation System. It defines the system's goals, features, functional and non-functional requirements, design constraints, and provides an initial schedule and budget.
1.2 Document Scope:
This document specifies the requirements for a Railway Reservation System, which enables efficient management of train reservations, ticketing, seat availability, fare calculation, schedule management, and passenger information. The system should prioritize user-friendliness, accuracy, and reliability.

1.3 Overview:
The Railway Reservation System serves as a comprehensive solution for railway operators to streamline the reservation and ticketing process. It leverages modern technology to provide a seamless and convenient experience for passengers.

2) General Description:
The Railway Reservation System provides users with an intuitive interface to search, book, and manage train reservations. It includes features such as seat availability checking, fare calculation, online ticket booking, cancellation and refund management, and real-time train schedule updates.

3) Functional Requirements:
The functional requirements of the Railway Reservation System include:

Train and seat availability checking
Online ticket booking and payment
Seat selection and reservation
Ticket cancellation and refund processing
Train schedule management
Passenger information management
Integration with payment gateways and travel agencies
Reporting and analytics for reservation statistics

4) Interface Requirements:
The Railway Reservation System should provide a user-friendly interface for passengers to search for train options, book tickets, and manage their reservations. It should also offer interfaces for railway administrators to manage train schedules, seat availability, and passenger information.

5) Performance Requirements:
The Railway Reservation System must handle a large number of concurrent users and provide fast response times for ticket booking, cancellation, and seat availability queries. The system should also be scalable to accommodate peak travel periods.

6) Design Constraints:
The Railway Reservation System should be designed using modern technology stacks and adhere to industry standards. It should ensure data security and privacy, as well as easy maintainability and upgradability.

7) Non-Functional Attributes:
The Railway Reservation System should exhibit reliability, security, and accessibility. It should provide a seamless user experience across different devices and browsers. The system should also be capable of recovering from failures and maintaining data integrity.

8) Preliminary Schedule and Budget:
The development of the Railway Reservation System is estimated to take 10 months, with a budget of $400,000. The schedule and budget will be periodically reviewed to ensure project progress and financial control.
